         <abstract>
            <p>Relating costs to risk factors has long been the ideal in providing for proposed ergonomie solutions. Utilizing the theory that all processes can be described in terms of cost, and likewise, in terms of ergonomie risk factors, then one should be able to correlate ergonomie risk factors to cost for a specific process or activity. Systems Engineering and Activity Based Costing Methods should be utilized to attribute costs to their respective source. The application of ergonomie risk factors are often activity dependent. The correlation of ergonomie risk factors to costs are displayed via case study.</p>
         </abstract>
